After initially playing backup to Antonio Daniels , [9] Parker was made a starter and made 77 regular season appearances in his rookie season, averaging 9.2 points , 4.3 assists and 2.6 rebounds in 29.4 minutes per game.

[3] When he played against the Los Angeles Clippers on 30 November 2001, he became the third French player ever to play in an NBA game, after Tariq Abdul-Wahad and Jerome Moiso .

In 2002-03, Parker played in all 82 regular season games as San Antonio's starting point guard [14] on a team that was largely revamped from previous years.

[14] He was also ranked 13th in the league in total assists, and was third among point guards in field goal percentage .

